cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DM, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a method for constructing classifiers using hyperbox fuzzy sets and multi-resolution hierarchical granular representations. This involves processing data at different levels of abstraction and handling uncertainty and incompleteness. These concepts are commonly associated with machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The paper also discusses experimental outcomes, which suggests a focus on data mining (cs.DM) and possibly social and information networks (cs.SI) as well.
